    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    AboutController
    Controller for managing the "About" section of the application.
    AboutModel
    A singleton class for managing application metadata such as the developer's information, release date, and version.
    AboutView
    Represents the "About" view in the application.
    BasicLogModel
    Defines the behavior of a basic logging model for managing log entries of various types.

    Controller class for managing confirmation dialogs.
    ConfirmPopup
    Represents a confirmation popup dialog.

    A specialized cell component for displaying filter items in a ListView with custom visual elements.

    Controller responsible for handling error messages and displaying them to the user through a popup view.
    ErrorModel
    A singleton class for managing error messages in the application.
    ErrorPopUp
    Represents an error popup dialog.
    EventHandler<T>
    Represents a functional interface for handling events.
    EventManager
    Central event management system implementing a type-safe event bus pattern.
    EventPublisher
    Represents a generic interface for publishing events.
    EventSubscriber
    Represents a generic interface for subscribing to and unsubscribing from events.
    ExitController
    The `ExitController` manages the application exit process, ensuring proper user confirmation before shutting down the application.
    ExportEvent
    Represents an event related to exporting images in the application.
    ExportEvent.ExportRequested
    Represents an event indicating that an export has been requested.
    ExportMenuItem
    Represents a menu component for exporting images in different formats.
    FileSystemView
    Represents a file system view for interacting with file and directory dialogs in the application.

    Controller class responsible for managing filters and handling filter-related events.
